<tool id="pca" name="PCA">
 
      <description>Principal Component Analysis</description>
      <command interpreter="Rscript">PCA.R $ExpressionSet $SelectedList  $pca</command>
      <inputs>
	 <param  name="ExpressionSet" type="data" label="ExpressionSet" />
	 <param  name="SelectedList" type="data" format="tabular" label="Selected List" />
      </inputs>
      <outputs>
      	 <data format="pdf" name="pca"   label="pca.pdf"   from_work_dir="pca.pdf" />  
      </outputs>
<help>

**What is does**

The PCA tool runs a Principal Components Analysis on the input selected gene expression dataset and constructs a plot of the top two principal components.
      </help>
</tool>
